      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ENTERTAINER (5) was strongly fancied last time but finished second (29.85), beaten 4 lengths. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Must come into calculations. PAY KEEPING (2) turned in a plain effort last time when fifth at this track over 520m behind Ritza Sophie (30.09) in a NG. Scored at her previous run. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. CONDO BANDIT (1) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.5 lengths (25.05) behind Taw Mystique at Goulburn. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Hard to beat again. MIGHTY HENRY (3) is always hard to beat when he races at this trip.",
